**Abstract:**
Research notes on Roger Bacon's unpublished works from the 1859 Brewer edition. Lists xeroxed passages from Opus Tertium on speculative vs. practical sciences (pp. 46-56), practical philosophy (pp. 79-83), and practical logic (pp. 103-105), as well as passages from Opus Minus on historical texts and the relationship between understanding philosophy and moral character.

**AI Recommendation:** Reference document for Bacon sources used in medieval philosophy research.

